This approach first gathers all panel IDs from the case object. Then, it uses a MongoDB aggregation pipeline to efficiently query the database and collect all associated gene symbols.

```python
def clinical_symbols(self, case_obj):
        """Return all the clinical gene symbols for a case."""
        panel_ids = [panel['panel_id'] for panel in case_obj['panels']]
        query = self.panel_collection.aggregate([
            {'$match': {'_id': {'$in': panel_ids}}},
            {'$unwind': '$genes'},
            {'$group': {'_id': '$genes.symbol'}}
        ])
        return set(item['_id'] for item in query)
```

The aggregation pipeline handles the deduplication automatically by using a group stage, resulting in a unique set of symbols.
